BT 1 0 0 1 0 51 Tm 12 TL /F2 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (I. The W-Lifespan Law:) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( W = T_operating/T_c predicts lifespan across species. Lower W = further from criticality = slower) Tj T* -0.026167 Tw (decoherence rate = longer life. The naked mole rat lifespan anomaly \(10x longer than body-mass prediction\) is explained by) Tj T* 0 Tw (W = 0.9299 \(lower than human 0.9394\). Elephant: W = 0.9224, long-lived. Mouse: W = 0.9538, short-lived. The correlation) Tj T* -0.036158 Tw (is: lifespan ~ \(1 - W\)^\(-nu/2\) where nu = 0.6301 \(3D Ising\). Testable against AnAge database \(2000+ species\). This predicts) Tj T* 0 Tw (that cryophilic organisms operating at lower W_effective will show systematically longer maximum lifespans.) Tj T* ET
